{"id": "POL115H5S20191", "code": "POL115H5S", "name": "Evidence and Argument in the Study of Politics", "description": "To understand politics in our information-abundant world, we need ways to make sense of the political information that surrounds us. In this course, we ask what makes for good evidence and what makes for convincing argument. We do so by raising a series of weekly topics on which there is a mass of available information - topics like climate change, political correctness, populism, and democracy promotion, among others - and discussing fundamentally different perspectives on each topic. In the end, students will develop a fuller sense of what constitutes a well-argued and evidence-supported analysis of the political. (24L, 12T)", "division": "University of Toronto Mississauga", "department": "Political Science", "prerequisites": "n/a", "exclusions": "", "level": 100, "campus": "UTM", "term": "2019 Winter", "breadths": [], "meeting_sections": [{"code": "L0101", "instructors": ["M Lippincott"], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 32400, "end": 39600, "duration": 7200, "location": "CC 1080"}], "size": 310, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T0101", "instructors": [], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 39600, "end": 43200, "duration": 3600, "location": "IB 379"}], "size": 30, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T0102", "instructors": [], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 39600, "end": 43200, "duration": 3600, "location": "IB 377"}], "size": 30, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T0103", "instructors": [], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 46800, "end": 50400, "duration": 3600, "location": "IB 379"}], "size": 30, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T0104", "instructors": [], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 46800, "end": 50400, "duration": 3600, "location": "IB 377"}], "size": 30, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T0105", "instructors": [], "times": [{"day": "MONDAY", "start": 50400, "end": 54000, "duration": 3600, "location": "IB 379"}], "size": 30, "enrolment": 0}, {"code": "T010